{"word":"πρωτόγονος","slug":"πρωτόγονος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πρωτόγονος</b></el> <el>(πρωτό-γονος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:γίγνομαι'><el>γίγνομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>first-born, firstling</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>; <el>φοῖνιξ πρ.</el> <i>first-created</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of rank, <el>πρ. οἶκοι</el> <i>high-born</i> houses, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>first-ordained</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}